# Byte-exact JSONC fixtures. The edge-case tests assert on EXACT bytes (a real
# UTF-8 BOM; genuine CRLF line endings), so the repo-root `* text=auto eol=lf`
# normalization must NOT touch these. `-text` makes git treat them as binary:
# no CRLF<->LF conversion and no BOM stripping, so a clone on any OS reads back
# the same bytes these tests were written against.
bom.json            -text
crlf-duplicate.json -text
